&lt;div&gt;The proposed development by reason of scale, siting and design would be an overly bulky, discordant addition which would appear overly dominant and would disrupt the rhythm of the street. The first floor side extension and ground-floor rear extension would cause unacceptable harm to the character, and appearance of the original dwelling and surrounding area. The accumulative impact of the proposal will be uncharacteristic to the local character and appear as a significant addition in bulk and mass to the dwelling. The proposed first-floor side extension fails to maintain a gap between the subject dwelling and neighbouring dwelling to the west and would therefore result in the loss of character and is considered harmful to the appearance of the house, built form of the semi-detached dwelling and character of the area.&amp;nbsp; As such, the proposed development is contrary to:&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: &quot; pt=&quot;&quot; sans&quot;,=&quot;&quot; sans-serif;&quot;=&quot;&quot;&gt;-
